        await adapter.approve_tool(\n                        message.get(\"tool_id\", \"\"),\n                        message.get(\"approved\", False)\n                    )\n                \n                case \"answer\":\n                    await adapter.answer_question(message.get(\"answer\", \"\"))\n                \n                case \"cancel\":\n                    await adapter.cancel()\n                \n                case _:\n                    logger.warning(\"Unknown message type: %s\", msg_type)\n                    await websocket.send_json({\n                        \"type\": \"error\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Unknown message type: {msg_type}\"\n                    })\n    \n    except WebSocketDisconnect:\n        logger.info(\"Client %s disconnected\", client_id)\n    except Exception:\n        logger.exception(\"WebSocket error\")\n    finally:\n        await connection_manager.disconnect(client_id)\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/agent_tui/web/routes/ws.py\ngit commit -m \"feat(web): add WebSocket endpoint for real-time agent communication\"\n```\n\n## Context\n\nThe WebSocket endpoint provides real-time bidirectional communication for the web interface. It uses the WebAdapter to dispatch agent events to the client.\n\nKey files to reference:\n- `src/agent_tui/services/web_adapter.py` - WebAdapter (already implemented)\n- `src/agent_tui/services/stub_agent.py` - StubAgent for testing\n- `src/agent_tui/web/state.py` - ConnectionState and connection_manager\n\nWork from: /home/shako/REPOS/Indie-Hacking/agent-tui\n\n## Your Job\n\n1. Implement the WebSocket endpoint\n2. Verify it imports correctly (python -c \"from agent_tui.web.routes.ws import router\")\n3. Commit your work\n4. Self-review\n5. Report back\n\n**Note:** No tests needed for this chunk - WebSocket testing is complex and the integration tests in Chunk 10 will cover the full flow.\n\n**Report Format:**\n- **Status:** DONE | DONE_WITH_CON